== Preparation ==

Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Drain and rinse half the @black beans{6.7%oz} (use the rest as you like).

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and @basmati rice{1/2%cup}. Stir until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add 3/4 cup water, 1 TBSP @white wine vinegar{5%tsp} (we sent more), and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} to pot. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and let simmer until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

Halve @cucumber{1} lengthwise, then slice into thin half-moons. Toss in a #medium bowl{} with 1 TBSP @kimchi hot sauce{4%oz} (we sent more), remaining vinegar, a large pinch of salt, and @sugar{1%tsp} until combined. Set aside.

In a #small bowl{}, stir @sour cream{4%tbsp} and 1 TBSP kimchi hot sauce (use less to taste). Season with salt.

Zest @lime{1} until you have 1 tsp zest, then cut into quarters. Heat @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @shredded carrots{4%oz} and cook, tossing, until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in half the lime zest and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Lower heat under pan to medium. Add remaining kimchi hot sauce and drained beans. Cook, stirring, until warmed, about ~{3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, toss together half the cucumber, half the carrots, scallion greens, and a squeeze of lime juice in another medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

Add remaining lime zest to rice in pot and fluff grains with a fork. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave on high until warm, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Divide half the rice between tortillas (serve the rest on the side or save for another use). Top with beans and remaining cucumbers and carrots. Roll into burritos, then cut each in half. Serve with crema, tossed veggies, and lime wedges on the side.